Kimberly<br>
You have not offended anyone here, we feel the same pain. <br>
I've been thinking, if the soldier buried there is identified, should we replace him with another unknown Vietnam soldier?<br>
Or should we leave it empty, symbolic of the emptiness we feel for those that are still missing.<br><br>
There can be no closure unless everyone comes home, leave it empty and it will echo loud on how America turned its back on Vietnam veterans, how politicians rushed to hush our need for recognition. <br><br>

